criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  patients willing to begin fixed multibracket therapy with metallic or ceramic
             brackets;

          -  full permanent dentition;

          -  enamel integrity, absence of traumatic or carious lesions, no pretreatment procedure
             performed with chemical agents;

          -  no previous orthodontic treatment with fixed vestibular appliances.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patients suffering from systemic diseases;

          -  patients taking medications that could alter periodontal conditions (NSAIDS, steroids,
             etc.);

          -  patients with low compliance;

          -  patients unable to give informed consent;

          -  presence of congenital enamel defects;

          -  extractions for orthodontic reasons;

          -  oral/orthognathic surgery.
